title: Smoked Haddock Kedgeree, Quails Eggs And Curried Mayonnaise
summary: Smoked Haddock Kedgeree, Quails Eggs And Curried Mayonnaise might be just the Scottish recipe you are searching for. This pescatarian recipe serves 3 and costs $4.21 per serving. This main course has 814 calories, 39g of protein, and 42g of fat per serving. 5 people have made this recipe and would make it again. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about 46 minutes. A mixture of rapeseed oil, mayonnaise, mild curry powder, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so scrumptious. To use up the lemon you could follow this main course with the Lemon Shortbread Cookies with Lemon Icing {A Tribute to Aunt Roxanne} as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 76%. This score is solid. Try Kedgeree (British Curried Rice With Smoked Haddock), Mini smoked haddock Scotch eggs with asparagus dippers & watercress mayonnaise, and Creamy smoked haddock & saffron kedgeree for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Haddock works really well with Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. The La Fiera Pinot Grigio with a 4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 7 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: La Fiera Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: This wine has a light straw color with green tints. It has a light floral and fruity bouquet featuring apples and pears. The palate is bright, fresh and dry showing nice balance and a lingering acidity perfect for a variety of lighter cuisine.Blend: 100% Pinot Grigio
